propertyObj.description: Configure the timer as per business operation needs

Link to the Customer Exit Integration Flow.  

Mandatory in case “Customer Exit Flow Enabled” is set to “true”  
   

For Example:  
   

/generic_customer_exit_process_direct
Indicates whether the Customer Exit flow is Enabled

Business partner number. If provided, this will be used as a SoldToParty customer for all BigCommerce orders. 

 
For Example: 
1234567

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Material Condition Code
propertyObj.description:
This is the used Condition Type to set up the promotions for the material/product in SAP S4HANA Public Cloud. 

 

For Example: 

 

ZM01

Indicates whether logging of Exceptions, as attachments, is enabled. 

 

Default Value: true 

 

Valid values: 

true 

false

Indicates whether logging of System Payloads is enabled. This is not recommended to be enabled in a live environment unless necessary. 

 

Valid values: 

true 

false

Link to the Customer Post-Exit Integration Flow. 

Mandatory in case “Customer Post-Exit Flow Enabled” is set to “true” 

For Example: 

/generic_post_exit_process_direct

Link to the Customer Pre-Exit Integration Flow. 

Mandatory in case “Customer Pre-Exit Flow Enabled” is set to “true” 

For Example: 

/generic_pre_exit_process_direct

This parameter can be used to narrow down the created outbound delivery for a Sales Order in client's SAP S4HANA Cloud Environment 

For Example: 

SubsequentDocumentCategory eq \'J\'

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Tax Condition Code
propertyObj.description:
Condition code for Tax amount, also need to allow manual input 

For Example: 

TTX1

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Shipping Condition Code
propertyObj.description:
The Condition Code for Shipping amount.  

For Example: 

ZFRH

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Discount Condition Code
propertyObj.description:
This is the Condition Code used to store the discount coming from BigCommerce. Customer can choose different one associated with his environment, but it needs to allow manual input. 

For Example: 

YK07

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Billing Text Code
propertyObj.description:
This is the code of the Billing Text in the Sales order Item Level located in the Text. This text is used to save the payment details coming from BigCommerce.

For Example: 

TX05

Default Language 

For Example: 

EN

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Partner Function Ship-To
propertyObj.description:
The Code for the Ship-To Partner Function 

For Example: 

 

SH

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Partner Function Bill-To
propertyObj.description:
The code for The Bill-To Partner Function 

For Example: 

 

BP

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Price Condition Code
propertyObj.description:
The default condition code for the Price comes from BigCommerce. The customer can choose a different one, but it needs to allow manual input. 

For Example: 

PPR0

The Payment Terms for the Customer 

For Example: 

0001

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Shipping Scenario Code
propertyObj.description:
Shipping Scenario Code  

For Example: 

01

Customer Division 

For Example: 

00

Customer Distribution Channel 

For Example: 

10

Customer Sales Organization 

 
For Example: 

3810

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Sales Order Type
propertyObj.description:
The Sales Order type 

For Example: 

OR
Indicates whether the Customer Pre-Exit flow is Enabled
Indicates whether the Customer Post-Exit flow is Enabled

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud Last Request Date
propertyObj.description:
This Date is used to define boundaries for the start for the replication flow. After that, the flow will save the latest date automatically and will use it to determine the delta for materials extract.
Example for a Valid Value  

1970-01-01T00:00:00Z

The status code for the BigCommerce Order. For a full list of available values, check the API Documentation 

 

Default Value: 11 (Awaiting Fulfillment)

Specify the SAP S/4HANA Cloud API Base URL 

 

For Example: 

https://xxxxxxx-api.s4hana.cloud.sap

The type of proxy you want to use for establishing connection with the OData V2 service.

Default value: Internet
Authentication method that you want to use for connecting to the OData V2 service.
Specify the name of the deployed User Credentials Security Material that holds the username and password used to authenticate with SAP S/4HANA Cloud

Keep this option selected (default setting). It ensures that your integration flow is protected against Cross-Site-Request-Forgery, a kind of attack where a malicious party can perform harmful actions by masquerading as the logged in user.

The option is enabled by default. This option enables the reuse of connection objects from the internal connection pool, which in turn improves the network turnaround time for multiple communications to a same end point.

This parameter will give the flow the correct address for the Create Partner flow. We Advise not to change its default value. 

For Example: 
/replicateSingleCustomerToS4HANA

Your BigCommerce base URL. The store hash part can be extracted from the BigCommerce dashboard URL: https://store-XXXXXX.mybigcommerce.com/manage/dashboard 

  

Example of a valid value:  

https://api.bigcommerce.com/stores/abcdef1234
Specify the name of the deployed Secure Parameter that holds the access token used to authorize with BigCommerce

propertyObj.key: BigCommerce Attach Error Details on Failure
propertyObj.description:
If selected, any errors encountered by the adapter will be output in a separate text attachment 

 

Default value: True

Specify the accepted response headers. Use a pipe “|”-separated list. Using “*” will accept all response headers 

Default value: *

Configure the session handling scope for HTTP based endpoints
Options:
None - Switched off
On Exchange - Each exchange corresponds to a single session
On Integration Flow - Only one session will be used across the whole integration flow
It is visible only when On-Premise is selected for Proxy type. Used to connect Cloud SAP Connector to your account.
It is visible only when Client Certificate is selected for Authentication. Enter the alias of the deployed private key.

This limit is used when we obtain information from BigCommerce and can affect performance.  

 

Example of a Valid Value:  

50

propertyObj.key: SAP S4HANA Cloud CPD Business Partner
propertyObj.description:
Business partner number. This must be provided and will be used as a SoldToParty for all BigCommerce orders placed by guest users.

For example: 

1234567
